Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["STBenchmark", "ObjectName",ExpressionUUID->"54365e7f-70e7-4ddb-966f-a59b4a4207a2"],

Cell[BoxData[GridBox[{
   {Cell[TextData[{
     StyleBox["STBenchmark[]", "TI"],
     " \[LineSeparator]runs the benchmark suite defined in mgDiagrams-style \
benchmark catalogue (embedded as $stBenchmarkCasesSource): a dependency check \
(see STDependencies[]) followed by the STIntegrate / STNIntegrate cases \
exercising the supported input forms and backends. Cases run sequentially in \
the main kernel; caches are cleared between cases so that one case's state \
cannot poison the next. The file ships two splits \\[LongDash] \"Short\" (10 \
cases, default, ~smoke test) and \"Long\" (21 cases, developer regression \
coverage); pick between them with the \"Suite\" option."
    }], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"44b80d4d-4c23-4483-a1b5-a3f2256dbd18"]},
   {Cell[TextData[{
     StyleBox["STBenchmark[selector]", "TI"],
     " \[LineSeparator]restricts the run to a subset (e.g. \"diagrams\", \
{\"nIntDiagrams\", 1 ;; 3}, or a list of case ids). Options: \"Suite\" -> \
\"Short\" | \"Long\" (which case list to load); \"Verify\" -> True | False \
(cross-check nIntDiagrams via STVerify); \"Display\" -> \"Stream\" | \"Silent\
\"; \"Baseline\" -> Automatic | None | _String (path to baseline JSON); \
\"UpdateBaseline\" -> True | False | Automatic (bake current run as the new \
baseline; Automatic writes only when no baseline exists yet); \"Report\" -> \
None | _String (write a Markdown report); \"SkipPackageCheck\" -> True | \
False. Returns Null; per-case details are stored in $STLastBenchmarkResults \
(a list of Associations) for programmatic access."
    }], "TableText",ExpressionUUID->"1ebeda3b-3aa0-4636-a116-58c7193e7c66"]}
  },
  GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Left}}},
  GridBoxItemSize->{
   "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}]], "Usage",
 CellID->1,ExpressionUUID->"7af5c634-118a-48b1-820d-7b9f67b63cf2"]
}, Open  ]],

